<2ND_LINE>PM-Weicker Stays Put,310</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Senate Posse Skipped 240-Pound Weicker in Pre-Dawn Republican
Roundup</HEAD>
<HEAD>With PM-Filibuster Bjt</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By CHRISTOPHER CALLAHAN</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>Associated Press Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Before Republican-hunting Capitol police
carried GOP Sen. Bob Packwood onto the Senate floor during
filibuster of a campaign finance bill, they found Sen. Lowell P.
Weicker Jr. sitting quietly in his office.
   But the Connecticut Republican, a political heavyweight in more
ways than one, was apparently too big for the posse led by Senate
Sergeant-at-Arms Henry Giugni to handle when they entered Weicker's
office at 12:45 a.m. Wednesday.
   ``I think Henry took a look at the 6-6 and 240 pounds and
figured it was a long trip from the Capitol Rotunda to the Senate
floor,'' Weicker said Thursday in a telephone interview. ``I could
see the wheels turning.
   ``Henry came in and indicated that I was arrested, and I told
him that was no time of day to arrest anybody and I was comfortably
ensconced on my couch and had no intention of moving,'' Weicker
said.
   Weicker quoted Giugni as saying on his way out the door,
``(expletive), I hate this job.''
   ``It was very good natured and there was no hint of
confrontation other than there he had been, here he was and here he
was going to stay,'' said Weicker aide Steve Snider. ``He and Henry
Giugni know each other very well.''
   Giugni did not return a series of telephone calls Thursday. An
aide said he would no longer talk about the bizarre night.
   Packwood, who was hauled off about 45 minutes later, is seven
inches shorter and 60 pounds lighter than Weicker.
   The incident occurred when Democrats, angered that Republicans
were trying to filibuster a campaign finance reform bill without
having a quorum on the Senate floor, ordered Giugni to forcibly
bring GOP members to the chamber. Democratic sponsors of the bill
have been unable to muster enough votes to end the filibuster.
</TEXT>
