<HEAD>Fair Weather Dominates the Nation</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By The Associated Press</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
   Isolated snow showers lingered in the Northeast today and a few
light rain showers dampened Northern California, but fair weather
prevailed across the nation.
   A weak storm moving across Lake Ontario was expected to drop 3
to 6 inches of snow on New York state east of the lake, and a snow
squall warning was in effect.
   Clouds extended from California to Texas and over Washington
state and Oregon. Partly cloudy skies prevailed from the Great
Lakes to the middle and northern Atlantic Coast.
   Today's forecast called for scattered snow showers across
eastern Upper Michigan, the eastern Great Lakes and upper Ohio
Valley; rain showers over the southern Pacific Coast and mild
weather for most of the nation, with mostly sunny or partly cloudy
skies.
   High temperatures were expected to be in the 50s or 60s across
much of the country; the 20s from northern sections of the Great
Lakes through northern and central New England; the 30s and 40s
from the eastern Dakotas and upper Mississippi Valley into the Ohio
Valley and the mid-Atlantic region; the 70s across Southern
California and from southern and eastern Texas into Oklahoma and
southwest Kansas; and around 80 degrees across the desert Southwest.
   The high for the nation Thursday was 88 degrees at Palm Springs,
Calif. Temperatures around the nation at 2 a.m. EST ranged from 4
degrees at Montpelier, Vt., to 68 degrees at Phoenix, Ariz.
   Other reports:
   _East: Atlanta 31 fair; Boston 24 fair; Buffalo 20 fair;
Charleston, S.C. 37 fair; Cincinnati 15 fair; Cleveland 22 partly
cloudy; Detroit 17 fair; Miami 52 fair; New York 25 fair;
Philadelphia 24 partly cloudy; Pittsburgh 18 snow; Portland, Maine
20 partly cloudy; Washington 28 partly cloudy.
   _Central: Bismarck 35 fair; Chicago 22 fair; Dallas-Fort Worth
48 fair; Denver 34 fair; Des Moines 34 fair; Indianapolis 20 fair;
Kansas City 32 fair; Minneapolis-St. Paul 32 fair; Nashville 24
fair; New Orleans 47 fair; St. Louis 30 fair.
   _West: Albuquerque 50 cloudy; Anchorage 37 windy; Las Vegas 52
partly cloudy; Los Angeles 61 partly cloudy; Phoenix 67 cloudy;
Salt Lake City 31 fair; San Diego 58 hazy; San Francisco 55 foggy;
Seattle 45 partly cloudy.
   _Canada: Montreal 19 partly cloudy; Toronto 18 snow.
