<HEAD>Share Prices Down In Early London Trading</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LONDON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Share prices fell in early trading on the London
Stock Exchange today after Thursday's drop on Wall Street.
   The Financial Times-Stock Exchange 100 index was down 8.8 points
at 1,773.6 at 9:45 a.m.
   When the market officially opened at 9 a.m., the index was down
1.3 points at 1,781.1.
   Dealers said prices started to recover near the official opening
on continued confidence in the British economy, but fell back
shortly afterwards.
   The early trend followed losses in New York Thursday, where the
Dow Jones industrial average fell 22.38 to 2,017.57, and gains in
Tokyo overnight, where the Nikkei index rose 64.52 to 25,165.18.
