<2ND_LINE>PM-Obit-Iacucci,0128</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>American Dies In Auto Accident During Italian Business Trip</HEAD>
<DATELINE>FLORENCE, Italy (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A top American wine merchant was killed
in a two-car collision near Siena, the U.S. consulate said today.
   Louis Iacucci, 52, of the New York City borough of Queens, was
taken Wednesday evening to a hospital in Siena, where he died four
hours later of abdominal injuries, a consulate official said.
   The official, who spoke on condition her name not be used,
quoted a Siena police report.
   Iacucci, an authority on Italian wines, owned Goldstar Wine and
Spirits in Forest Hills, Queens. He was on a trip from Grosseto to
Siena, two wine-producing areas in the province of Tuscany. The
other driver, an Italian, was unhurt, the consulate said.
