<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Here is the 53-41 roll call Friday by which
the Senate failed to shut off debate on a bill to limit campaign
spending.
   On this vote, a vote ``for'' was a vote to end the filibuster,
while a vote ``against'' was a vote to continue the debate. It
takes 60 votes to end a filibuster.
   There were 53 votes ``for'' and 41 votes ``against.''
