<HEAD>British Ag Minister to See US Officials, Farmers</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   John MacGregor, Great Britain's minister of
agriculture, will meet with U.S. officials and farmers during a
visit next month, the Agriculture Department said Friday.
   Deputy Secretary Peter C. Myers said MacGregor will be here
March 10-16 and will also visit St. Louis and Memphis, Tenn., where
the Briton ``hopes to meet with small groups of farmers and
agricultural leaders to learn more about U.S. agriculture,'' Myers
said.
