<2ND_LINE>AM-BRF--Reagan-Personnel,100</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Reagan Names D.C. Lawyer To Transportation Department Post</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   President Reagan on Friday announced his
intention to nominate Robert L. Pettit to be associate deputy
secretary of transportation, succeeding Jennifer Lynn Dorn.
   Since 1986, Pettit has been a partner with the law firm of
Wiley, Rein & Fielding in Washington. Before that, he was senior
legal adviser to Mary Dawson, a member of the Federal
Communications Commission, from 1982-86, and an associate with the
law firm of Fletcher, Heald & Holdreth, from 1978-82.
   Pettit, a 35-year-old native of Springfield, Mo., graduated from
the University of Missouri in 1974 and Duke University School of
Law in 1977.
