   Boredom, peer pressure and bad management
create a climate for widespread drug and alcohol use by the
nation's railroad workers, two crewmen involved in last year's
fatal Amtrak crash say.
   The former Conrail workers told the Senate Commerce Committee on
Thursday of co-workers who consumed as much as a case of beer a
day, brought bottles of liquor to work, or used marijuana, cocaine,
amphetamines and other drugs.
